    {
        "content": "<p>Do you know about <code>simp_rw</code>?</p>",
        "id": 460063635,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1723462505
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Nope, I haven't seen that being used yet in the book, so I haven't tried to use it. </p>\n<p>I always tend to assume that we can solve some of these exercises with what's been used in examples so far and maybe some high school level math, so I try to stick to that as much as I can (for better or worse sometimes, lol).</p>\n<p>I have started to take a look at Mathematics in Lean to try to get a better sense of how some of this stuff is working and what other tools I may have available, but I haven't gone too far into that book just yet either.</p>",
        "id": 460064888,
        "sender_full_name": "Jonatas Miguel",
        "timestamp": 1723463061
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm starting to wonder if it has something to do with the specific version of Lean v4 that I'm using. The version specified for the codebase seems to be v4.3.0, not sure if this is relevant or not though.</p>",
        "id": 461025484,
        "sender_full_name": "Jonatas Miguel",
        "timestamp": 1723483399
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can always try in the most recent Lean using the code sandbox (click the icon in the top right of any code block on zulip).</p>",
        "id": 461992883,
        "sender_full_name": "Kim Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1723512882
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Oops, you can't because you've forgotten to include your imports in your code block, and in this case it is Heather's custom tactics, which aren't available in the sandbox.)</p>",
        "id": 461992945,
        "sender_full_name": "Kim Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1723512927
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"260507\">@Heather Macbeth</span>, should we make the sandbox work with your repo? I don't see why it would be difficult?</p>",
        "id": 461992976,
        "sender_full_name": "Kim Morrison",
        "timestamp": 1723512952
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The error is because <code>rw</code> doesn't work for rewriting terms which appear \"under binders\", e.g. terms after <code>∀ x, </code> or <code>∃ x, </code>. I think the expected way to prove this exercise is using only \"logic\" tactics like <code>intro</code>, <code>constructor</code>, <code>use</code>, <code>by_cases</code>, <code>have</code>, <code>obtain</code>, <code>contradiction</code>, and <code>apply</code>.</p>",
        "id": 462439340,
        "sender_full_name": "Timo Carlin-Burns",
        "timestamp": 1723681693
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110087\">Kim Morrison</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/116395-maths/topic/Mechanics.20of.20Proof.20Exercise.205.2E3.2E6.2E3/near/461992976\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"260507\">Heather Macbeth</span>, should we make the sandbox work with your repo? I don't see why it would be difficult?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110087\">@Kim Morrison</span>  There are a few quirks, for example there are files from the repo which could not be imported, because they contain <a href=\"https://hrmacbeth.github.io/math2001/09_Sets.html#id18\">exercises with sorries in the statements</a>.</p>",
        "id": 462441210,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1723682793
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"495981\">@Jonatas Miguel</span> As Timo says, the solution I have in mind would replace this part of your proof</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"k\">obtain</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"n\">li</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"n\">ri</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">calc</span>\n<span class=\"w\">          </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">¬∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬¬</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rel</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">not_exists</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">          </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rel</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">not_not</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">haxPx</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">li</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hxPx</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>with only \"logic\" tactics, i.e. no use of <code>rel</code>.</p>\n<p>The proof of <code>not_exists</code> is in <a href=\"https://hrmacbeth.github.io/math2001/05_Logic.html#quantifier-logical-equivalence\">Example 5.16</a> and the proof of <code>not_not</code> is basically in <a href=\"https://hrmacbeth.github.io/math2001/05_Logic.html#id13\">Example 5.2.6</a>, so rather than invoking those lemmas by name in your proof, you can adapt the ideas from the proofs of those lemmas.</p>",
        "id": 462441550,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1723683040
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>By the way, the reason your code wasn't working on standard Mathlib is because Mathlib's <code>rel</code> doesn't handle <code>↔</code>.  This is for slightly subtle reasons -- related to the reason Yael suggested the <code>simp_rw</code> workaround -- so in the book I cheat by extending <code>rel</code> to special-case <code>↔</code>:<br>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/hrmacbeth/math2001/blob/main/Library/Tactic/Rel.lean\">https://github.com/hrmacbeth/math2001/blob/main/Library/Tactic/Rel.lean</a></p>",
        "id": 462441788,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1723683167
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Aah, I see. I had wondered if that was the case or not. I think one way to make that clearer is to state that we shouldn't be using any of those lemmas instead of referring only to the ones that we'd essentially be reimplementing. I'll go back to those exercises and rewrite my solutions.</p>",
        "id": 462442922,
        "sender_full_name": "Jonatas Miguel",
        "timestamp": 1723683678
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I hadn't realised that there was a way of using them in this exercise! :)</p>",
        "id": 462443107,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1723683732
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But now I think about it, here's how to take this idea to the extreme: <span aria-label=\"grinning\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f600\" role=\"img\" title=\"grinning\">:grinning:</span></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">calc</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">∀</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">simp_rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">not_not</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">simp_rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">not_exists</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">simp_rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">not_not</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(The <code>simp_rw</code> are standing in for <code>rel</code> on the math2001 repo, although I haven't tested it there.)</p>",
        "id": 462444401,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1723684160
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ok, finally got some time and finished rewriting those two exercises in chapter 5.3 where we were supposed to avoid using the lemmas.</p>\n<div class=\"spoiler-block\"><div class=\"spoiler-header\">\n<p>Exercise 5.3.6.2:</p>\n</div><div class=\"spoiler-content\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Q</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Prop</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Q</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∧</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Q</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hnPimpQ</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\">-- case ¬(P → Q) → P ∧ ¬Q</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">by_cases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hPanQ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\